iters, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan was born in 1435, in Wilton, Roxburghshire, Scotland. She had at least 1 son with Geoffrey Mawle."},"et":{"1435–":"1435–Surnud","1395–1465":"1395–1465","1460–1556":"1460–1556","1435–Female":"1435–Surnud","1435":"1435","1556":"1556","1465":"1465","1395":"1395","1460":"1460","Wilton, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Wilton, Roxburghshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1435–":"1435–Kuollut","1395–1465":"1395–1465","1460–1556":"1460–1556","1435–Female":"1435–Kuollut","1435":"1435","1556":"1556","1465":"1465","1395":"1395","1460":"1460","Wilton, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Wilton, Roxburghshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1435–":"1435–Décédée","1395–1465":"1395–1465","1460–1556":"1460–1556","1435–Female":"1435–Décédée","1435":"1435","1556":"1556","1465":"1465","1395":"1395","1460":"1460","Wilton, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Wilton, Roxburghshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Joan est née en 1435, à Wilton, Roxburghshire, Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Geoffrey Mawle."},"de":{"1435–":"1435–Verstorben","1395–1465":"1395–1465","1460–1556":"1460–1556","1435–Female":"1435–Verstorben","1435":"1435","1556":"1556","1465":"1465","1395":"1395","1460":"1460","Wilton, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Wilton, Roxburghshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Joan wurde 1435 in Wilton, Roxburghshire, Scotland geboren. Sie hatte mit Geoffrey Mawle mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1435–":"1435–Desede","1395–1465":"1395–1465","1460–1556":"1460